<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1874-08-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1874-08-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="151" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d151">
                    <head>No. 149.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Williams</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-08-29"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 29,
                            1874</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 179.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose, for your information and that of
                        Mr. Avery, a copy of an instruction of the 26th instant, No. 409,<note n="*" xml:id="d151fn1">See correspondence with the consul-general in
                            China.</note> addressed by this Department to George F. Seward, esq.,
                        the consul-general of the United States at Shanghai, in relation to
                        participation of citizens of the United States in the Japanese expedition to
                        Formosa.</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>